

get_Rx_errno(3N)                                 get_Rx_errno(3N)

SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [options] file -lnsl #include <rx.h>

       long get_Rx_errno(void);

       int set_Rx_errno(long value);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The  functions  get_Rx_errno and set_Rx_errno retrieve and
       set the value  of  Rx_errno  in  multi-threaded  programs.
       These  functions are needed in multi-threaded environments
       because each thread keeps its own copy of Rx_errno.

       The value of Rx_errno reflects an error resulting  from  a
       call to rexecve and related functions.

UUssaaggee
       While  get_Rx_errno  and set_Rx_errno are designed for use
       in multi-threaded applications, they are available for use
       in non-reentrant code and may be incorporated if a need is
       anticipated to convert to reentrant code later on.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       get_Rx_errno returns the value of Rx_errno,  or  RXE_NOER-
       RMEM  in  case it fails to allocate memory for the thread-
       specific copy of Rx_errno.

       set_Rx_errno sets Rx_errno to value,  and  returns  0  for
       success and -1 for failure.

